Progress is reported by Webpack&#39;s [`ProgressPlugin`](https://webpack.js.org/plugins/progress-plugin/), which Vue CLI [inserts only for non-production and non-test builds](https://github.com/vuejs/vue-cli/blob/6f085d3/packages/%40vue/cli-service/lib/config/dev.js#L19-L23) (since 3.x).

You could enable this plugin in [`&lt;root&gt;/vue.config.js`](https://cli.vuejs.org/config/#vue-config-js) with `devServer.progress=true` (currently [undocumented](https://cli.vuejs.org/config/#devserver)):

```js
module.exports = {
  devServer: {
    progress: true  // always show progress (even in production mode)
  }
}
```

Or in your `e2e.js`, you could insert the `ProgressPlugin` into the `Service` instance&#39;s `webpackChainFns[]` *after* `init()`:

```js
service.init(&quot;production&quot;)
service.webpackChainFns.push(config =&gt; {
  config
    .plugin(&quot;progress&quot;)
    .use(require(&quot;webpack/lib/ProgressPlugin&quot;))
})
```

